Part One: 1) Are there some days of the week where more accidents happen than on others (use variable DAY_WEEK)?

ggplot(acc, aes(DAY_WEEK)) + geom_bar()

It appears that most accidents occur on Saturday while monday has the least amount of accidents.

2) What time of the day do accidents happen (use variable HOUR)?

ggplot(acc, aes(HOUR)) + geom_bar() + xlim(0,24)
## Warning: Removed 262 rows containing non-finite values (stat_count).
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_bar).

Most accident occur later in the day with a peak around the 18 oclock mark (6pm). Additionally there are approxamently 260 accidents with a time of 99:99. I took this to mean the time was unknown which is why the value is not a vailed time this accidents are not shown on the graph.

3) What is the number of accidents with at least one drunk driver (use variable DRUNK_DR)?

numDrunkDrivers <- acc %>%
  filter(DRUNK_DR != 0) %>%
  summarise(n = n())

head(numDrunkDrivers)
##      n
## 1 8769

8769 accident invlolve a drunk driver.
